stream
BT
/F1 11 Tf
72 750 Td
(  CHANGED from Rev 1.0: capacity doubled from 1000 to 2000 events.) Tj
72 736 Td
(HAG-REQ-F010: Wake-up time from sleep mode shall not exceed 500 ms.) Tj
72 722 Td
(HAG-REQ-F011: The BMS firmware shall implement cybersecurity measures per ISO 21434.) Tj
72 708 Td
(  NEW in Rev 2.0. Secure boot, authenticated firmware updates, encrypted diagnostics.) Tj
72 694 Td
() Tj
72 680 Td
(4. Performance Requirements) Tj
72 666 Td
(HAG-REQ-P001: Cell measurement cycle time shall not exceed 10 ms.) Tj
72 652 Td
(HAG-REQ-P002: Supply voltage operating range: 9 V to 16 V.) Tj
72 638 Td
(HAG-REQ-P003: Quiescent current in sleep mode shall not exceed 500 microamp.) Tj
72 624 Td
(HAG-REQ-P004: MTBF shall be >= 50,000 operating hours.) Tj
72 610 Td
(HAG-REQ-P005: BMS PCB shall meet IP67 protection class.) Tj
72 596 Td
(  CHANGED from Rev 1.0: IP54 upgraded to IP67 per field feedback from Helios.) Tj
72 582 Td
() Tj
72 568 Td
(5. Safety Requirements \(ASIL-B\)) Tj
72 554 Td
(HAG-REQ-S001: BMS functional safety shall achieve ASIL-B per ISO 26262. Safety-critical.) Tj
72 540 Td
(HAG-REQ-S002: Safe state shall be entered within 5 ms upon fault detection. Safety-critical.) Tj
72 526 Td
(  CHANGED from Rev 1.0: response time tightened from 10 ms to 5 ms.) Tj
72 512 Td
(HAG-REQ-S003: Redundant voltage measurement hardware required for ASIL decomposition.) Tj
72 498 Td
(  Safety-critical. Two independent measurement channels required.) Tj
72 484 Td
(HAG-REQ-S004: Hardware watchdog shall reset BMS within 50 ms on software fault. Safety-critical.) Tj
ET

endstream
